         <abstract id="aspace_0dba0c5b699668a3c8d37739db9efbfd">Tyre Glen was a slave trader,
            planter, postmaster, and merchant in North Carolina. This collection consists largely of
            business papers, particularly of financial and legal documents concerning the slave
            trade in North Carolina, Virginia and Alabama as well as possibly other locations. In
            addition to copious information on slave trading in the 1830s and 1840s, the collection
            includes references to Glen's Union sympathies and claims for horses confiscated by the
            U.S. Army; farming; exemptions from the Confederate Army and other topics. </abstract>
         <physloc id="aspace_7ecbb694d011994514bf748136bca468">For current information on the
            location of these materials, please consult the Library's online catalog.</physloc>
